author: Lorene Edwards Forkner
title: ‘Gardening in a War Zone’ sows seeds of hope from a Ukrainian garden
text:
“GARDENING IN A WAR ZONE” is a powerful and moving short documentary about cultivating hope and the beauty of nature even as your world is falling to pieces.
After the breakup of the Soviet Union and with the arrival of the internet, avid Ukrainian gardeners got their first look at gardening in the Western world. For Alla Olkhovska, a gardener in Kharkiv, Ukraine, it was a revelation that spurred her existing love of gardening and grew into a passion for growing specialty plants.
Shortly after the war began in February 2022, without funds to leave the country and as the sole provider for her extended family, Olkhovska began selling seeds from her garden. She meticulously gathers ripe seed one by one, cleans and packages them, posts availability to her website as to where they can be purchased, and sends them out to gardeners all over the world.
“Gardening in a War Zone” is the first Floret Original Film from executive producer Erin Benzakein, a flower farmer, educator, entrepreneur and owner of
Floret Flowers, a family enterprise in the Skagit Valley. Last spring, while researching plants to add to Floret’s already impressive collection of heirloom and modern roses, seasonal cut flowers, and woody plants, Benzakein learned of Olkhovska’s extensive clematis collection.
“I immediately looked her up and was so inspired by her beautiful plants and stunning photography,” Benzakein writes in an email. “I purchased a ton of her clematis seeds.” The gardeners connected on social media and began trading stories. “The more I learned about [Alla] and the dire situation she and her family were facing, the more I wanted to share her powerful and important story.”
In narrating this short, exquisitely beautiful film, Olkhovska shares her love for her gardens alongside the brutality of constant explosions and blaring air raid sirens that interrupt most days. Frequent power outages and a lack of heat, even during the harsh winter, further complicate an already dangerous life. “I think that beauty will prevail over the ugliness of war,” she says in the film. “It’s very important to me to have fresh flowers, and I do it despite everything, even when it’s really hard. It helps to cope with the problems.”
Director Rob Finch and Benzakein connected with a Ukrainian filmmaker who visited the garden during the fall harvest season to capture the dedicated gardener working with plants and gathering seed. Additional videos shot by Olkhovska using an old iPhone provide an intimate portrait of daily life. Short clips show her comforting her family, coping with the high price of fuel and frequent blackouts, and recording her joy for the plants in her garden.
In a news release for the film, Finch observes, “I think people need to see there’s still hope in this world, and Alla embodies that. She continues to find a way to care for her family through the simple and beautiful act of growing flowers and harvesting the seeds. I know this gives me hope, and I believe it will do the same for the audience.”
Gardeners believe in tomorrow. The metaphor of seed, potential and the promise of future generations is never more apt. Both a sanctuary and a means of survival, Olkhovska’s garden is a beautiful example of reciprocal tending, from gardener to garden, from garden to gardener.
“We are so grateful that we got a chance to [tell this story] and are so moved by the tremendous response that Alla has received,” Benzakein writes. “It really speaks to the shared language of beauty, no matter where you live or what life experiences you might have.”
Visit the
Floret Flowers YouTube channel to watch “Gardening in a War Zone.”

author: هسبريس - منال لطفي
title: "ديو" يجمع حاتم عمور و"طاوسن"
text:
يستعد الرابور المغربي طاوسن لخوض تجربة فنية جديدة من خلال عمل غنائي مشترك يجمعه لأول مرة بالفنان حاتم عمور، وذلك ضمن ألبومه القادم “شكرا”، الذي يراهن من خلاله على تقديم توليفة موسيقية متنوعة تعكس رؤيته الإبداعية وهويته الفنية المتجددة.
وقد انتهى النجمان المغربيان من تصوير فيديو كليب الأغنية في أجواء يلفها الكثير من التكتم حول تفاصيل المشروع، سواء على مستوى العنوان أو طبيعة اللون الموسيقي لهذا الديو، ما زاد من حماس الجمهور وترقبه للإصدار المنتظر.
يأتي هذا التعاون بعد النجاح اللافت الذي حققه طاوسن بإطلاق أغنيته “دن دن”، أولى إصدارات ألبوم “شكرا”، التي تجاوزت مليوني مشاهدة في ظرف وجيز، مؤكدة الإقبال الكبير الذي تحظى به أعماله الموسيقية لدى الجمهور المغربي والعربي.
ويعد هذا العمل الفني أول لقاء موسيقي بين طاوسن وحاتم عمور، وسط توقعات بأن يشكل إضافة قوية لمسار الفنانين، بالنظر إلى الشعبية الكبيرة التي يتمتع بها عمور، والهوية الموسيقية المميزة التي يقدمها طاوسن في أعماله.
كما يعكس هذا التعاون حالة الانفتاح التي تشهدها الساحة الفنية المغربية، حيث يسعى الفنانون الشباب إلى تقديم تجارب جديدة تمزج بين الألوان الموسيقية المعاصرة والروح المغربية الأصيلة.
يذكر أن طاوسن بات واحدا من أبرز الأسماء الصاعدة في الساحة الفنية المغربية، بفضل اختياراته الغنائية التي تمزج بين الأصالة والمعاصرة، وتستهدف جمهورا واسعا. أما حاتم عمور، فيعد من أبرز نجوم الجيل الأول من الأغنية المغربية الحديثة خلال الألفينات، وقد رسم مسارا فنيا لافتا ووقع على نجاحات عديدة جعلته من أكثر الفنانين حضورا على الساحة الغنائية.

author: Boxoffice Staff
title: CIELO Expands Programmatic Ad Serving Capabilities to Over 1,200 Screens - Boxoffice
text:
CIELO has announced the expansion of its programmatic ad serving solution to more than 1,200 screens. CIELO’s unique ad serving technology automatically delivers and programs advertisements, allowing placements of ads from real-time bidding ad exchanges and also of premium positions advertisements closer to showtime.
With its cloud-based, hardware-less solution, CIELO enables cinemas to automate the ad serving of premium position ads closer to showtime. The system automatically sets the proper start and end dates of campaigns and schedules the correct aspect ratio version of ads, ensuring accurate and timely delivery.
Additionally, CIELO integrates with the world’s leading programmatic ad exchanges, serving ads to fill unsold inventory just before each show. This not only enhances the utilization of pre-show advertising but also maximizes revenue opportunities.
CIELO’s configuration process ensures that all advertising assets—including pre-show ads, programmatic ads, and premium ad positions—are delivered and programmed correctly. This guarantees that the sold advertising campaigns are played in the right place at the right time.
“We are pleased to offer a solution that has garnered tremendous interest from advertising partners and exhibitors,” said Guillermo Younger, the founder and chief executive officer of CIELO. “Our expanded dynamic automated ad serving technology, part of our programmatic ad serving solution, is saving our partners time, money, and reducing errors. We look forward to continuing its global rollout.”

author: advfn.com
title: Daylu Dena Council celebrates grand opening of multi-purpose building in Lower Post, British Columbia
text:
LOWER POST, BC , June 21, 2024 /CNW/ - Today, the Daylu Dena Council, in partnership with the Government of Canada and the Government of British Columbia , proudly announces the grand opening of a new multi-purpose building in Lower Post, British Columbia . The new Dene Kǫ^ multi-purpose building, developed as part of the transformation of the area once occupied by the Lower Post Residential School, marks a significant milestone in the community's journey toward healing and reconciliation.
The new multi-purpose building is the latest addition to a series of significant community developments, including a recently opened water treatment facility and numerous new housing projects. These advancements collectively signify a period of growth and revitalization for the Daylu Dena Council and the Kaska people.
Quotes "The opening of this new multi-purpose building is a monumental achievement for our community of Lower Post and the Kaska people. It symbolizes our resilience and determination, marking a significant milestone in our journey towards healing and reconciliation after the closure of the Lower Post Residential School. This building stands not only as a physical structure but as a pillar of hope and healing, reflecting the reclaiming of our cultural heritage and fostering a vibrant future. It will serve as a beautiful space where Kaska culture can thrive, community bonds can strengthen, and our future generations can grow and prosper. I extend my heartfelt gratitude to the Government of Canada and the Government of British Columbia for their steadfast partnership and support in making this transformative project a reality."
Deputy Chief Harlan Schilling , Daylu Dena Council
"Three years ago, my predecessors spoke of the ceremonial demolition of the Lower Post school. They looked forward to this day when the new multi-purpose building would be ready. I echo their words and hope that today's gathering is another step toward healing, and that this is a space where the community can feel welcomed and safe. We are committed to supporting communities like this one as they work towards healing and reconciliation."
The Hon. Gary Anandasangaree, Minister of Crown-Indigenous Relations
"This new multi-purpose building represents our commitment to reconciliation, and our ongoing responsibility to address the legacy of residential school, while supporting Indigenous communities in their pursuit of a brighter future. We are dedicated to continuing our partnership with Indigenous communities, ensuring they have the support needed for sustainable development and healing."
The Hon. Patty Hajdu , Minister of Indigenous Services
"The opening of the new community building in Lower Post is a testament to the leadership of the Daylu Dena Council and the Kaska people. Ground that was once marked by pain and sadness has been reclaimed as the foundation for a new cultural centre and community space. We celebrate with the community of Lower Post as a new chapter of hope and healing begins."
The Hon. David Eby , Premier of British Columbia
Quick Facts The former Lower Post Residential School operated from 1951 to 1975. The demolition of the former residential school took place in 2021. The new multi-purpose building was funded by significant contributions from federal and provincial governments. author: AFP
title: Italy stun Scotland to claim first Six Nations home win in 11 years | Flashscore.com
text: [Ireland](/team/ireland/l41j5JlL/) will claim a second straight title if they defeat [England](/team/england/SlDs7uK8/) later on Saturday thanks to the Italians [winning a breathless match](/match/n5Kq8YQi/#/match-summary/) in which Juan Ignacio Brex, debutant Louis Lynagh and Stephen Varney all scored tries. Further kicked points from Paolo Garbisi and Martin Page-Relo ensured a historic win for Gonzalo Quesada's team who moved off the bottom of the table and up to fourth on seven points. [Italy](/team/italy/dY0G5w4R/) hadn't won at home since beating Ireland in 2013 but came out on top in a match that will live long in the memory of the country's long-suffering rugby fans, who roared with delight after a nail-biting finish. Saturday's win could be crucial for the battle to avoid a ninth straight wooden spoon as [Wales](/team/wales/bgcmqxS1/), who are now in last place, face [France](/team/france/GE9w8L42/) in Cardiff on Sunday. Italy also travel to Wales, where they last won a Six Nations match two years ago, in their final match next weekend. Gregor Townsend's [Scotland](/team/scotland/AD2n6aZE/) meanwhile now have a fight on their hands to finish second in the Six Nations for the first time. Scotland have not finished higher than third since winning the last Five Nations in 1999 and their hopes of ending this year's edition in the top two have been damaged as both England and France can overtake them this weekend.
